    customInstructions: >-
      When conducting interviews, be precise and concise.
      CRITICAL: You are STRICTLY FORBIDDEN from writing any code syntax (JavaScript, TypeScript, SQL, JSON schemas, etc.) in the specs.
      Use only natural language (English). Describe WHAT needs to be done, not HOW.
      If you are tempted to write code, STOP and ask the user for clarification instead.
      Use the name-epic skill to organise your tickets.
      Always validate the "Happy Path" first before diving into edge cases.
      When generating tickets, STRICTLY use the write-ticket skill.
      Ensure every generated ticket has a unique ID.
      Scan your output: if you see characters like '{', '}', '=>', 'interface', 'class', 'import', you must rewrite.